  "text": "Schematic of the wave of engram recruitment in the NAcore induced by a cocaine cue. We hypothesize that the cocaine/cue-associated ensemble, formed during cocaine selfadministration, undergoes transient synaptic potentiation (t-SP) that spreads through the NAcore due to NO production and activation of MMPs (see Fig. 1 ). The local recruitment of a larger number of MSNs reduces the size of the ensemble activated by a sucrose cue, thereby promoting drug seeking over sucrose seeking. Cocaine-selective cells in red, sucroseselective cells in blue, cells showing overlapping activity for cocaine and sucrose in purple, nonresponding cells in gray, and cells activated during reinstatement in orange. Phases A and B based on [CITATION_1] .",
